				<div class="postbody">
				I'm hearing...
<br />

<br />
The entire Winsock API and a good chunk of networking code, and some chunks of NetBIOS.
<br />
All of the APIs for Internet Information Server 5.
<br />
The entire rendering engine and interface layer for IE6.
<br />
All of Microsoft's Encrypted File System code.
<br />
All of the NTFS code.
<br />
The entire windows kernel.
<br />
The entire user shell.
<br />
Lots of core APIs.
<br />

<br />
To me it sounds like if it came on 40 CDs, someone knew just which one to grab to do the most damage. That spells nasty, nasty worms and virii if it's accurate.
<br />

<br />
I'm also hearing the comments in the source code are a riot, and that apparently its quality is pretty bad. I'll look forward to reading a summary of a professional programmer on the whole mess as soon as someone gets around to writing it.<br />
